                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">
                        <locus from="2r" to="95v"/>
                        <seg type="script">Eighteenth-century script.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (vivid vermilion).</seg>
                        <desc>Fine, careful. The handwriting remains uniform throughout the manuscript and is characterized by finely shaped, slender and upright letters.</desc>
                       
                        <seg type="rubrication">Divine names; a few lines on the incipit page of <ref target="#p2_i1">Text 1, Unit 2</ref> and <ref target="#p2_i2">Text 2, Unit 2</ref> alternating with black lines; 
                           two initial lines of each daily section of <ref target="#p2_i1">Text 1, Unit 2</ref>; elements of the punctuation signs;
                           elements of Ethiopic numerals; the word <foreign>mǝʿrāf</foreign> ‘chapter’ e.g., <locus target="#84ra, #85vb #90rb"/>; days of the week: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘሠሉሥ፡</foreign> <locus target="#15r"/>, 
                           <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘዓርብ፡</foreign> <locus target="#53r"/>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘእሑድ፡</foreign> <locus target="#72r"/> in the margins.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e4">            
                           <desc type="findingAid">Daily readings are indicated with the names of the days of the week written in the upper margin, encircled by dot lines, in a secondary hand:
                              <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘሰኑይ፡</foreign> e.g., <locus target="#2r #3r #78r"/>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘሠሉሥ፡</foreign> <locus target="#16r #79r"/>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘረቡዕ፡</foreign> e.g., <locus target="#28r #29r #80r"/>;
                              <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘሐሙስ፡</foreign> <locus target="#40r #83r"/>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘዓርብ፡</foreign> <locus target="#85r"/>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘቀዳሚት፡</foreign> <locus target="#65r #88r"/>,
                              <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘእሑድ፡</foreign> <locus target="#90r"/>. The following names are written in red in the <ref type="hand" corresp="#h2">main Hand 2</ref>: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘሠሉሥ፡</foreign> <locus target="#15r"/>, 
                              <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘዓርብ፡</foreign> <locus target="#53r"/>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘእሑድ፡</foreign> <locus target="#72r"/>. </desc>
